	(text "1. Dangerous current flows from motor back into motor\n2. Voltage increases due to internal resistance\n3. MCU senses voltage (threshold) and activates resistor \n4. Thick resistors convert power into heat\n5. MCU senses safe voltage (hysterisis) deactivates resistor\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 407.924 120.904 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
				(color 4 0 0 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "f2158224-0878-4c69-a5f9-cefbf921d2d0")
	)
	(text "Communication with all other peripherals\nDoes the control logic\nADC1 used specifically incase WiFi enabled\nPSRAM pins IO35-37 may be available\n=> hence use N16\nIO45-46 Strapping Pins - if used pull-down \n46 and pull-up 45 during start\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 265.43 205.74 0)
		(effects
